<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-02-20T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-02-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="1" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">710.G Peace/22: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-20T18:00:00-05:00">February 20, 1934—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>28. Department understands anti-war treaty is no longer open to signature
                            and that non-signatory States may become parties only by adherence.</p>
                        <p>In order that Department may proceed pursuant to resolution of Montevideo
                            Conference of December 16, 1933, obtain and forward certified copy of
                            the pact as early as possible.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>